parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to hesitate or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or loses power when accelerating
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the RPMs fluctuate or surge
the vehicle stalls or fails to restart
the transmission warning light illuminates
and the vehicle may jerk or shudder when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and hesitation can cause the vehicle to lose power or accelerate suddenly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power or accelerates suddenly
the RPMs fluctuate or surge
the vehicle stalls or fails to restart
and the transmission warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission fluid leaks and odor can cause the transmission to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fluid leaks or smells like radiator fluid
the passenger floorboards are wet and have a weird texture
and the transmission warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, increase RPM, and display warning messages, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses motive power
the RPM increases suddenly
the speedometer becomes inoperable
the brake system malfunctions
the "Service Transmission" message is displayed
the vehicle struggles to crank
and the vehicle requires a wait of 2-3 minutes before cranking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
slow acceleration
jerking or hesitation when accelerating
feeling like the vehicle is stuck in a low gear
sudden acceleration after initial hesitation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping or hesitation can cause loss of power, difficulty merging or climbing hills, and increased wear on transmission components, leading to premature failure.
symptoms: Jerking or hesitation when accelerating
feeling like the vehicle is stuck in a low gear
slow acceleration
sudden acceleration after initial hesitation.
